(0,-334.08 260420,-334.08)Methodology
(0,-161.28 266784,-161.28)Analytical approaches to estimating the effect of transportation investment on economic
(0,-167.04 273075,-167.04)development started out using cost-benefit analysis. More recently the profession has
(870.912,7530.97 391.388,7530.97)Transportation in the New Millennium
(4303.76,0 442.191,0)4
(-5123.52,-437.76 6825.75,-437.76)turned to production and cost functions as a way to include a wider range of benefits.
(0,-167.04 13549.1,-167.04)However the profession is only now coming to grips with transportation infrastructure as a
(0,-164.16 20057.8,-164.16)spatial concept. Transportation facilities are located in a specific place they provide
(0,-167.04 26949.6,-167.04)services to businesses (and households) within a specific geographical area and their use is
(0,-164.16 33140.5,-164.16)directly related to moving goods and people between two points. Furthermore because
(0,-167.04 39456.4,-167.04)transportation services are provided within a network (or system) what happens in one
(0,-164.16 45992.5,-164.16)place affects what happens in another. Therefore the appropriate methodology has to take
(0,-167.04 52675.6,-167.04)into account not only the spatial relations as the goods and people are shipped between two
(0,-164.16 57669.5,-164.16)points but also how these shipments fit into a network (or system).
(216,-167.04 64279.1,-167.04)Current production (cost) function analyses fall short of this goal. They typically do not
(-216,-164.16 68787.7,-164.16)incorporate the spatial correspondence nor do they encompass 
(3648.96,0 70183.1,0)systemwide effects.
(-3648.96,-167.04 76460.5,-167.04)Therefore the direction for the future is to build models that can provide this more
(0,-164.16 82764.1,-164.16)comprehensive view while preserving the spatial correspondence between transportation
(0,-167.04 85481.3,-167.04)infrastructure and economic activity.
(216,-164.16 91760.3,-164.16)There is increasing interest among state and regional agencies in improving analytic
(-216,-167.04 94551,-167.04)approaches to estimation of equity or 
